{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5135905f-6b18-423d-a549-ef3dbbb396b1","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory, so here's general guidance for the switch:\n\n### Key Changes for NuGet Trusted Publishing (OIDC)\n\n**1. Add `id-token: write` permission** to your job:\n```yaml\npermissions:\n  id-token: write   # Required for OIDC\n  contents: read\n```\n\n**2. Replace the `dotnet nuget push` step.** Remove the `--api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}` flag and instead use the `--source` with a trusted publisher configuration:\n```yaml\n- name: Push to NuGet\n  run: dotnet nuget push \"**/*.nupkg\" --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**3. Configure the NuGet.org side:**\n- Go to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → Your Package → Trusted Publishers**\n- Add a new GitHub Actions trusted publisher with:\n  - **Repository owner** (your GitHub org/user)\n  - **Repository name**\n  - **Workflow filename** (e.g., `publish.yml`)\n  - Optionally restrict to a specific **branch/tag** or **environment**\n\n**4. (Recommended) Use a GitHub environment** for an extra layer of protection:\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    environment: nuget-publish   # matches what you set on nuget.org\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write\n      contents: read\n```\n\n**5. Remove** the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret from your repo settings once verified.\n\n### Summary of diff\n```diff\n jobs:\n   publish:\n     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n+    environment: nuget-publish\n+    permissions:\n+      id-token: write\n+      contents: read\n     steps:\n       - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n       - uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4\n       # ... build/pack steps ...\n       - name: Push to NuGet\n-        run: dotnet nuget push \"**/*.nupkg\" --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }} --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n+        run: dotnet nuget push \"**/*.nupkg\" --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\nThe OIDC token is automatically sent by `dotnet nuget push` when no API key is provided and the NuGet source supports trusted publishing. No extra action or token-exchange step is needed — `setup-dotnet@v4` handles the plumbing.\n\nIf you share your workflow file, I can make the exact edits for you.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"86cfbd79-0234-4971-8491-451118f57ed3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There are no files in the working directory. The user is asking a general question about switching from NuGet API key-based publishing to OIDC trusted publishing in GitHub Actions. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":711,"requestId":"0FC6:E1CFB:17EDDF2:1B18418:69E81AC2"},"id":"7e723227-d42d-4b08-8e62-e35f5089d42a","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:48:16.502Z","parentId":"693fdcce-0a9c-40a1-ba59-3cfe80825ef1"}
